The paper deals with a problem of blind calibration for linear random sensing models, which involves recovering an unknown signal from its projections on sub-Gaussian random vectors subject to an unknown positive multiplicative factor (or gain). This problem is related to topics such as compressed sensing, machine learning, and signal processing, which are covered by several arXiv CS sub-categories. Specifically, cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely category, as it deals with the mathematical foundations of information processing, including signal processing and compression. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely, as the paper discusses optimization algorithms for solving the blind calibration problem. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is another possible category, as the paper presents numerical experiments in an imaging context. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) are less likely but still possible, as they deal with topics such as optimization, algorithms, and numerical methods, which are relevant to the paper.
